      "code": "def min_kbeautiful_with_digits(n_str, allowed):\n    # Find minimum number >= n using only digits in allowed\n    # allowed is a sorted list of digit chars\n    # First digit can't be 0\n    n = len(n_str)\n    \n    def solve(pos, tight, digits):\n        # Try to build number of same length as n_str\n        if pos == n:\n            return ''.join(digits)\n        \n        lo = n_str[pos] if tight else '0'\n        for d in allowed:\n            if d < lo:\n                continue\n            if pos == 0 and d == '0':\n                continue\n            new_tight = tight and (d == lo)\n            # Fill rest with min allowed digit\n            if not new_tight:\n                rest = min(allowed) * (n - pos - 1)\n                return ''.join(digits) + d + rest\n            else:\n                result = solve(pos + 1, True, digits + [d])\n                if result is not None:\n                    return result\n        return None\n    \n    result = solve(0, True, [])\n    if result is not None:\n        return int(result)\n    \n    # Need longer number: smallest (n+1)-digit number using allowed\n    new_len = n + 1\n    first = min(d for d in allowed if d != '0')\n    rest = min(allowed) * (new_len - 1)\n    return int(first + rest)",
